VL  - 71
IS  - 5
KW  - Nonparametric estimation
KW  - nonadditive random term
KW  - shape restrictions
KW  - monotonicity
KW  - homogeneity
KW  - conditional distributions
KW  - nonseparable models
KW  - conditional quantiles
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00452
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We present estimators for nonparametric functions that are nonadditive in unobservable random terms. The distributions of the unobservable random terms are assumed to be unknown. We show that when a nonadditive, nonparametric function is strictly monotone in an unobservable random term, and it satisfies some other properties that may be implied by economic theory, such as homogeneity of degree one or separability, the function and the distribution of the unobservable random term are identified. We also present convenient normalizations, to use when the properties of the function, other than strict monotonicity in the unobservable random term, are unknown. The estimators for the nonparametric function and for the distribution of the unobservable random term are shown to be consistent and asymptotically normal. We extend the results to functions that depend on a multivariate random term. The results of a limited simulation study are presented.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Equilibrium Wage-Tenure Contracts
AU  - Burdett, Ken
AU  - Coles, Melvyn
